add(E) - Method in class pt.queues.FifoLifoQueue
Deprecated.
If the calling thread already has a local queue, or the calling thread is registered as a worker thread, then this call is equivalent to FifoLifoQueue.addLocal(Object). Otherwise, the call is equivalent to FifoLifoQueue.addGlobal(Object). It is therefore recommended to explicitly use FifoLifoQueue.addLocal(Object) or FifoLifoQueue.addGlobal(Object) to ensure the correct intention is performed.

enqueueReadyTask(TaskID<?>) - Method in class pt.runtime.AbstractTaskPool
 
enqueueReadyTask(TaskID) - Method in class pt.runtime.TaskpoolFIFOWorkSharing
Enqueues a task that is ready to be executed to one of the following task pools.
1- If the task can be executed by any thread, and is multi-task, it is enqueued to the globalMultiTask task pool.
2- If the task can be executed by any thread, but is not multi-task it is enqueued to the globalOneOffTask task pool.
3- If the task cannot be executed by any thread, it is enqueued to the local privateQueue of the thread in charge of executing the task.
enqueueReadyTask(TaskID<?>) - Method in class pt.runtime.TaskpoolLIFOWorkStealing
When enqueuing a task in the WorkStealing policy, if the task is not able to be executed on any arbitrary thread, regardless of the type of enqueuing thread it will be enqueued to the privateQueue of the thread in charge of executing that task.
enqueueReadyTask(TaskID<?>) - Method in class pt.runtime.TaskpoolMixedScheduling
When enqueuing tasks under the Mixed Scheduling policy, if a task cannot be executed by arbitrary threads, it will be enqueued to the privateQueue of the thread in charge of executing it.

TaskpoolMixedScheduling - Class in pt.runtime
The mixed scheduling policy is a combination of Work Stealing and Work Sharing policies, such that when enqueuing a task, if the enqueuing thread is a worker thread, the Work Stealing policy is used, and if the enqueuing thread is a non-worker thread, the Work Sharing policy is used!

A worker thread potentially prefers to execute tasks from its own localOneOffTask queue before helping with the global shared queue!
TaskpoolMixedScheduling() - Constructor for class pt.runtime.TaskpoolMixedScheduling
